Lets understand the columns first, what represents what actually¶

In [ ]:
'''
age =      how old is the person
gender =   1(male) & 0(female)
cp =       chest pain (4 values)
trestbps = resting bloodpressure values in mmhg
chol =     cholestrol level in mg/dl unit
fps =      fbs that is fasting blood sugar. it supposed to be 120mg/dl. if >120mg 1(true), or < 120 0(false)
restECG =  electrocardiographics values i.e : 0(normal), 1(abnormality) & 2(abnormality in left ventricular hyperthropy)
the lach = the max heart rate achieved
exang =    discomfort in chest, 1(yes), 0(no)
oldpeak =  kinda like depression outta blue when you exercise
slope =    3 values, 1,2 & 3 that are unsloping, flat and downsloping respectively
ca =       number of major vassels
thal =     displays the thalassemia, 3 = normal, 6 = fixed defect & 7 = reversible defect
class =    tells use whether the person is suffering from a heart desease 0(no), >0(yes) even shows its severity .
'''

lets set this "?" values with mode values, most occured value in the data for that column¶

In [ ]:
df.loc[(df["thal"]!="3") & (df["thal"]!="6") & (df["thal"]!="7"), "thal"] = df["thal"].mode()
df.loc[(df["ca"]!="3") & (df["ca"]!="2") & (df["ca"]!="1") & (df["ca"]!="0"),"ca"] = df["ca"].mode()
df["thal"] = pd.to_numeric(df["thal"])
df["ca"] = pd.to_numeric(df["ca"])
df.describe()
